1
00:00:02,069 --> 00:00:03,668
<i>[ TV: Man ]</i>
<i>GOOD MORNING, WASHINGTON.</i>

2
00:00:03,737 --> 00:00:05,670
<i>IT'S A SUNNY NEW DAY</i>
<i>HERE IN THE NATION'S CAPITAL,</i>

3
00:00:05,740 --> 00:00:07,672
BUT DON'T PUT AWAY
THOSE UMBRELLAS JUST YET,

4
00:00:07,742 --> 00:00:09,575
AS THERE'S A STORM
MOVING UP THE SEABOARD.

5
00:00:09,643 --> 00:00:12,177
<i>THE FIVE-DAY FORECAST</i>
<i>WILL FOLLOW TODAY'S</i>
<i>WASHINGTON REPORT.</i>

6
00:00:12,246 --> 00:00:14,179
<i> [ TV: Woman ]</i>
<i> WE'RE AT SECRET SERVICE</i>
<i> HEADQUARTERS...</i>

7
00:00:14,248 --> 00:00:16,181
FOR TODAY'S
WASHINGTON REPORT,

8
00:00:16,250 --> 00:00:20,318
WHERE OFFICIALS ARE TRYING
TO PIECE TOGETHER THE FINAL
HOURS OF TODD BAXTER,

9
00:00:20,387 --> 00:00:24,823
A YOUNG AGENT WHOSE BODY WAS
RECOVERED FROM THE POTOMAC RIVER
JUST LAST NIGHT.

10
00:00:24,892 --> 00:00:26,825
TODD.

11
00:00:26,894 --> 00:00:30,028
<i>[ Panting ]</i>

12
00:00:32,332 --> 00:00:34,332
[ Panting Continues ]

13
00:00:41,275 --> 00:00:43,875
<i>[ Man Shouting ]</i>
<i>JAROD! JAROD!</i>

14
00:00:53,954 --> 00:00:56,088
MIKE! THROUGH HERE!

15
00:00:57,157 --> 00:00:59,558
-<i> STOP!</i>
- [ Shouting, Indistinct ]

16
00:01:01,829 --> 00:01:04,462
<i>THERE HE IS! GET HIM!</i>

17
00:01:15,342 --> 00:01:17,609
STOP! WAIT! WAIT!

18
00:01:17,678 --> 00:01:21,779
WILL YOU HELP ME, PLEASE?
MY CAR IS BROKEN DOWN
AND I NEED A RIDE.

19
00:01:25,286 --> 00:01:28,653
- PLEASE?
- ALL RIGHT. HOP IN.

20
00:01:39,032 --> 00:01:40,965
[ Beeps ]

21
00:01:41,035 --> 00:01:44,036
GET ME MR. PARKER.
THE PRETENDER HAS ESCAPED.

22
00:01:52,479 --> 00:01:54,412
I'M FREE.

23
00:01:54,481 --> 00:01:56,648
I'M TODD-- BAXTER.

24
00:01:58,785 --> 00:02:00,852
JAROD.
JAROD.

25
00:02:02,089 --> 00:02:05,623
GOT A LAST NAME?
JUST JAROD.

26
00:02:05,692 --> 00:02:09,527
JUST JAROD, HUH?
HOW ABOUT THEM APPLES.

27
00:02:09,596 --> 00:02:12,097
[ Chuckles ]
APPLES?

28
00:02:15,603 --> 00:02:19,470
I, UH-- I DON'T KNOW
HOW I CAN EVER THANK YOU.

29
00:02:19,539 --> 00:02:23,708
OH, JUST SOMEDAY DOWN THE ROAD
DO SOMETHIN' NICE FOR SOMEBODY.

30
00:02:23,777 --> 00:02:27,345
THE SECRET SERVICE
IS BAFFLED BY
THE APPARENT SUICIDE.

31
00:02:27,414 --> 00:02:30,449
AFTER JUST
THREE-AND-A-HALF SHORT YEARS
AS AN AGENT,

32
00:02:30,517 --> 00:02:34,152
HOW DID SUCH
A PROMISING YOUNG MAN
END UP DEAD IN THE POTOMAC?

33
00:02:34,221 --> 00:02:38,022
<i> A QUESTION</i>
<i> THAT MAY NEVER BE ANSWERED.</i>

34
00:02:38,091 --> 00:02:41,226
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>
<i>THERE ARE PRETENDERS AMONG US.</i>

35
00:02:41,295 --> 00:02:43,228
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>I WAS TAKEN FROM MY FAMILY.</i>

36
00:02:43,297 --> 00:02:46,865
<i>THIRTY-SIX HOURS AND HE'S</i>
<i>ALREADY DEMONSTRATING MORE</i>
<i>TALENT THAN ANY OF OUR OTHERS.</i>

37
00:02:46,934 --> 00:02:50,335
<i>HOW MANY PEOPLE DIED</i>
<i>BECAUSE OF WHAT I THOUGHT UP?</i>

38
00:02:50,404 --> 00:02:53,839
SINCE I BROKE OUT,
I'VE SPENT EVERY MOMENT
SEARCHING FOR MY PAST.

39
00:02:53,908 --> 00:02:56,107
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE'S A PRETENDER--</i>

40
00:02:56,176 --> 00:02:58,944
<i>A GENIUS WHO CAN BECOME</i>
<i>ANYONE THAT HE WANTS TO BE.</i>

41
00:02:59,013 --> 00:03:01,746
-<i> THE CENTRE WANTS HIM ALIVE.</i>
- PREFERABLY.

42
00:03:01,815 --> 00:03:04,749
<i>- [ Miss Parker ] HE DEFENDS</i>
<i>  THE WEAK AND ABUSED.</i>
<i>- [ Jarod ] LIFE'S A GIFT.</i>

43
00:03:16,530 --> 00:03:18,997
-<i> YOU A DOCTOR?</i>
- I AM TODAY.

44
00:03:27,874 --> 00:03:30,809
<i>[ TV: Woman ]</i>
<i>MORE DETAILS EMERGING</i>
<i>IN THE APPARENT SUICIDE...</i>

45
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:32,811
<i>OF YOUNG SECRET SERVICE AGENT</i>
<i>TODD BAXTER,</i>

46
00:03:32,879 --> 00:03:36,814
WHO SPENT THE FINAL HOURS
OF HIS LIFE AT THIS D.C. HOTEL,
THE RIVER GLEN.

47
00:03:36,883 --> 00:03:39,418
<i>SOURCES SAY HE JUMPED</i>
<i>TO HIS DEATH IN THE POTOMAC...</i>

48
00:03:39,486 --> 00:03:42,287
AFTER A NIGHT OF DRUGS
AND DEPRESSION.

49
00:03:42,356 --> 00:03:46,925
<i>HOWEVER, FRIENDS AND FAMILY</i>
<i>WE SPOKE WITH SAY THIS IS NOT</i>
<i>THE TODD BAXTER THEY KNEW.</i>

50
00:03:46,994 --> 00:03:49,261
I'M GONNA
MAKE A DIFFERENCE.

51
00:03:50,664 --> 00:03:53,598
DOES THAT SOUND HOKEY?

52
00:03:53,667 --> 00:03:57,569
HOKEY?
IS THAT A SPORTING EVENT?

53
00:03:57,638 --> 00:04:00,405
[ Laughs ]
YEAH.

54
00:04:00,473 --> 00:04:04,075
ANYHOW, ALL MY LIFE
I'VE KNOWN THAT, UH,

55
00:04:04,144 --> 00:04:06,278
D.C.'S
WHERE THINGS GET DONE.

56
00:04:07,314 --> 00:04:09,247
IT'S A TOUGH TOWN
AND ALL THAT,

57
00:04:09,315 --> 00:04:13,651
BUT WITH SMARTS
AND HARD WORK,
A GUY CAN--

58
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:16,388
CHANGE THE WORLD.

59
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:20,258
<i> BUT WHAT CHANGED</i>
<i> TODD BAXTER?</i>

60
00:04:20,327 --> 00:04:22,828
WAS IT THE PRESSURE OF LIFE
INSIDE THE BELTWAY,

61
00:04:22,896 --> 00:04:25,463
<i> THE DEMANDING YEARS</i>
<i> IN THE SECRET SERVICE?</i>

62
00:04:25,532 --> 00:04:28,266
<i> THE ANSWERS</i>
<i> ARE THROUGH THOSE DOORS.</i>

63
00:04:28,335 --> 00:04:31,469
<i>[ Radio:</i>
<i>  Dispatcher, Indistinct ]</i>

64
00:04:33,573 --> 00:04:36,040
<i>[ Elevator Bell Dings ]</i>

65
00:04:36,109 --> 00:04:38,009
AGENT HOLDER?
YEAH?

66
00:04:38,078 --> 00:04:40,778
- SPECIAL AGENT WILKES.
- OH, RIGHT, RIGHT, RIGHT.

67
00:04:40,848 --> 00:04:43,781
THE BEHAVIORAL SCIENCE GUY.
YES, I JUST GOT IN
FROM THE AIRPORT.

68
00:04:43,851 --> 00:04:46,784
I BET YOU DIDN'T HAVE
LUNCH, EITHER, DID YOU?
HERE. YOU HUNGRY?

69
00:04:46,853 --> 00:04:51,222
"CUP O' SOUP.
A MEAL IN A MINUTE." THAT'S
A RATHER CLEVER IDEA, ISN'T IT?

70
00:04:51,291 --> 00:04:54,993
IDEA? ARE YOU FROM
THE SEATTLE OFFICE OR MARS?
SOMEWHERE IN BETWEEN.

71
00:04:55,061 --> 00:04:57,662
WELL, I BET THE BOSS
WANTS TO SEE YA. TALBOT.

72
00:04:57,731 --> 00:04:59,831
<i> HE'S GOT THE PLACE BUZZING</i>
<i> OVER THE BAXTER THING.</i>

73
00:04:59,900 --> 00:05:03,367
YOU KNEW TODD?
YEAH. CAN'T BELIEVE HE'D
DO SOMETHING LIKE THIS.

74
00:05:03,436 --> 00:05:05,369
NEITHER CAN I.

75
00:05:05,438 --> 00:05:08,306
-<i> WILKES. ELLIS TALBOT.</i>
- SIR.

76
00:05:08,375 --> 00:05:10,308
SEATTLE FAXED ME
YOUR PAPERS THIS MORNING.

77
00:05:10,377 --> 00:05:13,511
I COULD USE A MAN
WITH YOUR EXPERTISE
ABOUT NOW. FOLLOW ME.

78
00:05:15,949 --> 00:05:18,883
<i> THE MAID CALLED</i>
<i> THE D.C. COPS THIS MORNING</i>
<i> AND THEY CALLED THE BUREAU.</i>

79
00:05:18,952 --> 00:05:20,885
F.B.I.'S RUNNING THINGS.

80
00:05:20,954 --> 00:05:23,387
HOOVER BOYS ARE LOOKIN'
AT BAXTER'S BODY NOW.

81
00:05:23,457 --> 00:05:25,890
FROM WHAT I UNDERSTAND,
HE'D BEEN IN THE POTOMAC
ABOUT A WEEK.

82
00:05:25,959 --> 00:05:28,893
HE PUT A "DO NOT DISTURB"
SIGN ON THE DOOR,

83
00:05:28,962 --> 00:05:31,529
WHICH IS WHY IT TOOK
THE HOTEL PEOPLE SO LONG
TO FINALLY GET CURIOUS.

84
00:05:31,598 --> 00:05:33,364
<i> [ Holder ]</i>
<i> WHICH FITS WITH</i>
<i> THE REST OF THE STORY.</i>

85
00:05:33,433 --> 00:05:36,367
<i> THE NIGHT TODD</i>
<i> CHECKED IN HERE,</i>
<i> WITNESSES DOWNSTAIRS SAY...</i>

86
00:05:36,437 --> 00:05:39,837
THAT HE MET UP WITH AN OLD
GIRLFRIEND IN THE BAR, THEY
CAME HERE FOR A LITTLE SEX...

87
00:05:39,906 --> 00:05:42,040
AND A LOT OF HEROIN.

88
00:05:42,109 --> 00:05:44,042
HAS ANYONE QUESTIONED
THE GIRLFRIEND?

89
00:05:44,110 --> 00:05:46,044
<i>THE FEDS ARE STILL</i>
<i>LOOKING FOR HER,</i>

90
00:05:46,112 --> 00:05:49,047
BUT INDICATIONS ARE
SHE WAS LONG GONE BEFORE
TODD WENT ON HIS BENDER.

91
00:05:49,115 --> 00:05:51,749
AND JUMPED.

92
00:05:51,818 --> 00:05:56,354
<i>[ Talbot ] DEMONS LIKE HIS,</i>
<i>I SOMETIMES WONDER IF I EVER</i>
<i>KNEW THE REAL TODD BAXTER.</i>

93
00:06:01,762 --> 00:06:03,795
SURE YOU WANT
TO GET OUT HERE?

94
00:06:05,232 --> 00:06:07,466
YES.

95
00:06:07,534 --> 00:06:09,868
THIS WILL BE FINE.
ALL RIGHT.

96
00:06:09,936 --> 00:06:13,138
YOUR CAR DIDN'T REALLY
BREAK DOWN, DID IT?

97
00:06:13,207 --> 00:06:15,006
NO.

98
00:06:16,009 --> 00:06:18,076
WHY DID YOU HELP ME?

99
00:06:20,614 --> 00:06:23,148
MY GUT TOLD ME
TO TRUST YOU.

100
00:06:24,284 --> 00:06:26,584
WAIT A SECOND.

101
00:06:26,653 --> 00:06:28,586
THERE YOU GO.

102
00:06:28,655 --> 00:06:31,389
OH, NO. I-I COULDN'T POSSIBLY.
YOU'VE HELPED ME
TOO MUCH ALREADY.

103
00:06:31,457 --> 00:06:33,792
FORGET IT.
HAVE AN ICE CREAM CONE
ON ME.

104
00:06:35,528 --> 00:06:37,829
ICE CREAM?

105
00:06:37,898 --> 00:06:39,831
IS IT GOOD?

106
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:41,900
[ Chuckles ]
YEAH, IT'S VERY GOOD.

107
00:06:43,803 --> 00:06:47,805
LOOK, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT CAVE YOU'VE BEEN
LIVIN' IN, JAROD, BUT...

108
00:06:47,874 --> 00:06:49,808
YOU'RE EVER IN D.C.,
LOOK ME UP.

109
00:06:49,876 --> 00:06:51,609
I WILL.

110
00:06:53,079 --> 00:06:55,447
THANK YOU.

111
00:06:58,051 --> 00:06:59,850
<i>JAROD?</i>

112
00:06:59,919 --> 00:07:02,988
YOU TWO WORK WITH THE FEDS
IF YOU HAVE TO,
BUT REPORT ONLY TO ME.

113
00:07:03,056 --> 00:07:05,790
SO WHAT IS IT
YOU'RE NOT TELLING ME?

114
00:07:05,859 --> 00:07:10,628
F.B.I.'S FLOATING A THEORY
THAT THIS WAS A HOMICIDE.
THAT'S WHERE YOU COME IN.

115
00:07:10,697 --> 00:07:14,699
BAXTER'S SUICIDE'S EMBARRASSING
ENOUGH WITHOUT FAR-FETCHED
SPECULATION IT WAS A MURDER.

116
00:07:14,767 --> 00:07:16,367
<i>YOU'RE THE</i>
<i>BEHAVIORAL SCIENCE EXPERT.</i>

117
00:07:16,436 --> 00:07:19,304
GET THEM TO SEE THE TRUTH
ABOUT TODD'S
PSYCHOLOGICAL TROUBLES.

118
00:07:20,540 --> 00:07:22,941
<i>THE TRUTH</i>
<i>IS ALL ANY OF US WANT.</i>

119
00:07:29,817 --> 00:07:32,050
-<i> AGENT TED HOLDER.</i>
- HI.

120
00:07:32,118 --> 00:07:34,219
<i> THIS IS SPECIAL AGENT</i>
<i> JAROD WILKES.</i>

121
00:07:34,287 --> 00:07:37,122
BAILEY MALONE,
VIOLENT CRIMES TASK FORCE.

122
00:07:37,190 --> 00:07:39,156
V.C.T.F.
THE BUREAU'S FINEST.

123
00:07:40,793 --> 00:07:43,027
<i>I BROUGHT THE BAXTER</i>
<i>AUTOPSY FILES.</i>

124
00:07:43,096 --> 00:07:46,097
YOU BOYS HAVE
SOME CATCHING UP TO DO.

125
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:54,238
[ Muttering ]
DADDY?
I JUST HEARD.

126
00:07:54,307 --> 00:07:57,308
OH, THERE'S NOTHIN' TO FEAR.
THE DOCTORS JUST WANT THE BABY
FOR OBSERVATION.

127
00:07:57,376 --> 00:07:59,978
YOUR LITTLE BROTHER'S
GONNA BE JUST FINE.

128
00:08:00,047 --> 00:08:04,916
AFTER ALL, YOU HELPED
MY NEW SON INTO THIS WORLD,
GOT ME BACK TO MY OLD DESK.

129
00:08:04,984 --> 00:08:07,919
I'VE NEVER BEEN MORE PROUD
TO BE YOUR FATHER.

130
00:08:07,988 --> 00:08:11,256
OH, YOU GOT THAT LOOK
IN YOUR EYE.

131
00:08:11,324 --> 00:08:15,460
WHAT LIE HAS JAROD
BEEN TELLIN' YOU NOW?
IT'S NOT JAROD.

132
00:08:15,528 --> 00:08:17,528
IT'S ME.

133
00:08:19,999 --> 00:08:23,534
I DON'T KNOW, IT JUST--
[ Sighs ]

134
00:08:23,603 --> 00:08:26,871
SO MUCH HAS HAPPENED
IN THE LAST FEW WEEKS.

135
00:08:26,940 --> 00:08:30,741
BRIDGET DYING,
YOU COMING HOME, THE NEW BABY.

136
00:08:30,811 --> 00:08:34,612
<i>AH, I UNDERSTAND. YEAH.</i>
<i>YOU WANT THINGS TO BE DIFFERENT.</i>

137
00:08:34,681 --> 00:08:37,916
<i>LISTEN, COME HERE.</i>
<i>COME HERE.</i>

138
00:08:39,185 --> 00:08:42,120
YOU MUST NEVER LOSE YOUR DESIRE
TO GET JAROD BACK.

139
00:08:42,188 --> 00:08:46,224
THE NEW CHILD IS THE FUTURE
OF THE FAMILY, BUT JAROD
IS THE FUTURE OF THE CENTRE.

140
00:08:46,293 --> 00:08:48,192
WHY?

141
00:08:48,262 --> 00:08:50,128
HE'S OUR GREATEST ACHIEVEMENT,
OUR BIGGEST ASSET.

142
00:08:50,196 --> 00:08:53,864
HOWEVER, CONSIDER YOUR LIFE
OFFICIALLY CHANGED.

143
00:08:53,933 --> 00:08:56,901
IT'S A BRAND-NEW DAY
AT THE CENTRE.

144
00:08:56,970 --> 00:08:59,337
[ Chuckles ]
[ Kiss ]

145
00:09:03,643 --> 00:09:07,479
MY ATTEMPTS AT CROSS-POLLINATION
APPEAR TO BE SUCCESSFUL.

146
00:09:09,883 --> 00:09:11,883
VERY GOOD.

147
00:09:25,999 --> 00:09:29,467
LIES! DAMN LIES!

148
00:09:29,536 --> 00:09:32,003
LIES!

149
00:09:32,071 --> 00:09:34,139
<i> [ Jarod ]</i>
<i> THEY FINISHED</i>
<i> THE AUTOPSY ALREADY?</i>

150
00:09:34,207 --> 00:09:37,142
YES, IT'S ALL THERE
IN THE REPORT.
OH, AND GET THIS--

151
00:09:37,210 --> 00:09:40,145
MALONE TELLS ME THEY'RE NOT
JUST THINKING MURDER. THEY'RE
THINKING SIGNATURE KILLER.

152
00:09:40,213 --> 00:09:42,147
A SIGNATURE KILLER?
YEAH.

153
00:09:42,215 --> 00:09:45,150
WELL, APPARENTLY
THEIR PROFILER HAS A THEORY.
PROFILER?

154
00:09:45,218 --> 00:09:47,218
<i> [ Woman ]</i>
<i> THAT'S ME.</i>
<i> [ Knocking ]</i>

155
00:09:51,157 --> 00:09:54,526
- WERE YOU EXPECTING
SOMEONE ELSE?
- CALL IT DÉJÀ VU.

156
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:56,294
<i>WITH A TWIST ENDING.</i>

157
00:09:57,864 --> 00:09:59,664
JAROD WILKES.
RACHEL BURKE.

158
00:09:59,733 --> 00:10:01,665
- AGENT TED HOLDER.
- NICE TO MEET YOU.

159
00:10:01,735 --> 00:10:05,636
NOT TO BE RUDE, BUT ISN'T
YOUR SIGNATURE KILLER THEORY
A BIT PRESUMPTUOUS?

160
00:10:07,407 --> 00:10:10,642
WELL, IT'S JUST THAT.
IT'S A THEORY. BUT THERE'S
EVIDENCE TO SUPPORT IT.

161
00:10:10,711 --> 00:10:13,645
- LIKE?
- LIKE OUR AUTOPSY.

162
00:10:13,714 --> 00:10:16,648
IT CONFIRMS THAT TODD BAXTER
DID NOT DIE FROM A JUMP.

163
00:10:16,717 --> 00:10:19,150
HE WAS STRANGLED TO DEATH.
PROBABLY A PIANO WIRE.

164
00:10:19,219 --> 00:10:21,686
AND DESPITE A WEEK
IN THE POTOMAC,
WE FOUND THESE.

165
00:10:21,754 --> 00:10:24,488
- LIGATURE MARKS.
-<i> ON BOTH WRISTS.</i>

166
00:10:24,557 --> 00:10:27,691
NOT EXACTLY
CONSISTENT WITH SUICIDE.
NOT TO BE RUDE.

167
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:31,296
<i> AND HE WAS DRUGGED,</i>
<i> AND THERE IS EVIDENCE</i>
<i> OF SEXUAL ACTIVITY.</i>

168
00:10:31,364 --> 00:10:35,199
<i>HE MAY HAVE A SEXUAL NEED</i>
<i>TO BE TIED UP,</i>
<i>MAYBE EVEN ASPHYXIATED.</i>

169
00:10:35,268 --> 00:10:37,234
[ Phone Rings ]

170
00:10:45,245 --> 00:10:48,012
OR SOMEONE ELSE TIED HIM UP.

171
00:10:48,081 --> 00:10:50,014
YOUR SIGNATURE KILLER?

172
00:10:50,083 --> 00:10:52,650
- YEAH. IT'S JUST, UH--
- INSTINCT.

173
00:10:54,187 --> 00:10:56,187
SOMETHIN' LIKE THAT.

174
00:10:57,523 --> 00:11:00,524
THEY'VE LOCATED
TODD'S GIRLFRIEND,
AN EMILY SADLER.

175
00:11:00,593 --> 00:11:03,461
I'D LIKE TO
QUESTION HER MYSELF.

176
00:11:03,529 --> 00:11:06,831
- I'LL KEEP YOU IN THE LOOP.
- I LOOK FORWARD TO THAT.

177
00:11:14,774 --> 00:11:17,709
<i> [ Woman ]</i>
<i> TODD AND I</i>
<i> MET AT COLUMBIA.</i>

178
00:11:17,778 --> 00:11:21,479
<i> I STUDIED JOURNALISM,</i>
<i> AND HE WAS</i>
<i> A CRIMINOLOGY MAJOR.</i>

179
00:11:23,182 --> 00:11:28,052
<i> WHAT THEY SAY</i>
<i> ABOUT TODD IS TRUE.</i>
<i> HE WAS A REALLY GOOD GUY.</i>

180
00:11:28,121 --> 00:11:30,588
BUT HE HAD DEMONS.

181
00:11:30,657 --> 00:11:32,857
WHAT KIND OF DEMONS?

182
00:11:32,926 --> 00:11:35,359
THE KIND
HE COULDN'T BEAT.

183
00:11:35,429 --> 00:11:38,362
AND THIS TOWN
MADE IT WORSE.

184
00:11:38,432 --> 00:11:40,731
I'D NEVER SEEN HIM
THAT WRECKED.

185
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:43,467
-HE WAS IN
A BAD PLACE THAT NIGHT.
-HE HAD A DRUG HABIT, DIDN'T HE?

186
00:11:43,536 --> 00:11:45,370
YES.

187
00:11:47,541 --> 00:11:50,141
IT HAUNTED HIM.

188
00:11:51,444 --> 00:11:53,911
DID YOU TRY TO HELP HIM?

189
00:11:53,980 --> 00:11:56,947
WELL, WHAT DO YOU THINK
I WAS DOING THAT NIGHT?

190
00:11:57,016 --> 00:12:00,952
THAT'S WHY I WENT UPSTAIRS.
I WAS ALWAYS TRYIN'
TO HELP HIM.

191
00:12:01,021 --> 00:12:06,190
BUT THEN HE
PULLED OUT THE DRUGS,
AND HE STARTED DRINKING.

192
00:12:07,627 --> 00:12:10,662
AND WE STARTED FIGHTING.
SOME THINGS WERE SAID,
SO I LEFT.

193
00:12:10,730 --> 00:12:13,965
SO YOU JUST... WALKED OUT.

194
00:12:15,035 --> 00:12:16,834
NOW THAT'S<i> MY</i> DEMON.

195
00:12:23,309 --> 00:12:26,678
SO, IN YOUR MIND,
TODD BAXTER
WAS PERFECTLY CAPABLE...

196
00:12:26,746 --> 00:12:29,246
OF JUMPING OFF THAT BALCONY?

197
00:12:30,417 --> 00:12:32,149
YEAH.

198
00:12:32,218 --> 00:12:35,153
HE WAS ALWAYS
GOING TOO FAR.

199
00:12:35,222 --> 00:12:37,222
THAT'S THE WAY HE WAS.

200
00:12:39,492 --> 00:12:41,826
UNLESS YOU KNOW
SOMETHING I DON'T.

201
00:12:42,929 --> 00:12:44,695
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>THIS CAN'T BE RIGHT.</i>

202
00:12:48,601 --> 00:12:51,035
SYDNEY WOULDN'T
HAVE TRASHED THESE.

203
00:12:51,104 --> 00:12:53,037
THEY'RE LIKE THERAPY FOR HIM.

204
00:12:53,106 --> 00:12:55,106
HO-HO. HELLO.

205
00:12:56,743 --> 00:12:59,110
[ Computer: Sydney ]
DAMN LIES!

206
00:13:00,847 --> 00:13:03,614
<i>ALWAYS KNEW</i>
<i>HE WAS A MAD SCIENTIST.</i>

207
00:13:03,683 --> 00:13:07,384
- THE CENTRE DOES THAT TO YOU.
- GO BACK TO
BEFORE HE FREAKS OUT.

208
00:13:07,454 --> 00:13:09,454
OH.

209
00:13:10,289 --> 00:13:12,290
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>ANGELO.</i>

210
00:13:12,358 --> 00:13:16,060
- ZOOM IN AND FREEZE IT.
-<i> [ Broots ] IT'S A WATCH</i>
<i> IN A CENTRE BAG.</i>

211
00:13:16,129 --> 00:13:18,529
ANGELO MUST HAVE DUG IT OUT
OF THE CENTRE ARCHIVES.

212
00:13:18,598 --> 00:13:21,899
AND BEING AN EMPATH,
HE HAD TO KNOW THE EFFECT
IT WOULD HAVE ON SYD.

213
00:13:21,968 --> 00:13:23,667
I HATE SEEING HIM LIKE THIS.

214
00:13:23,736 --> 00:13:27,838
<i>[ Exhales ]</i>
<i>HOW MANY BLACK HOLES</i>
<i>HAS SYDNEY HELPED ME OUT OF?</i>

215
00:13:27,907 --> 00:13:30,674
WHY DIDN'T YOU COME TO ME?

216
00:13:30,743 --> 00:13:33,344
<i>[ Talbot ]</i>
<i>YOU GOT 48 HOURS</i>
<i>TO FIND THE TRUTH.</i>

217
00:13:33,413 --> 00:13:36,681
THE F.B.I. WANTS TO
CHASE THEORIES, THEY CAN DO IT
TILL THEIR BADGES FALL OFF.

218
00:13:36,750 --> 00:13:41,219
BUT I CAN TELL YOU, I WILL NOT
HAVE MY DIVISION WASTING
RESOURCES ON AGENT BAXTER.

219
00:13:41,287 --> 00:13:44,222
TELL JERRY
WE'RE IN, PLEASE.
SIR, HE IS ONE OF OUR OWN.

220
00:13:44,291 --> 00:13:46,224
THAT'S NOT THE ISSUE.

221
00:13:46,293 --> 00:13:49,227
THIS WHOLE MESS
HAS PUT A SPOTLIGHT ON US,
AND IT'S A BAD ONE.

222
00:13:49,296 --> 00:13:51,229
ARE YOU SUGGESTING
THAT THE F.B.I. IS LYING?

223
00:13:51,298 --> 00:13:53,430
NO. I'M SAYING
AGENT BAXTER WAS LYING.

224
00:13:53,499 --> 00:13:55,432
<i> FOR ALL WE KNOW,</i>
<i> A HEROIN DEALER KILLED HIM.</i>

225
00:13:55,501 --> 00:13:58,435
IT'S BAD ENOUGH
THAT THIS DIDN'T SHOW UP
ON A BACKGROUND CHECK.

226
00:13:58,505 --> 00:14:01,872
NOW WE HAVE TO FIND OUT THE KID
HAD A MILLION SICK HABITS.
A MILLION AND ONE.

227
00:14:01,941 --> 00:14:04,241
JERRY LINDEN,
OFFICE OF COMMUNICATIONS.

228
00:14:04,310 --> 00:14:06,043
SPECIAL AGENT WILKES.

229
00:14:06,112 --> 00:14:09,046
PLEASURE.
IF A REPORTER CALLS YOU,
SEND HIM TO JERRY.

230
00:14:09,115 --> 00:14:12,316
THANK YOU, SIR.
DO NOT LEAK THIS.
IT'S NOT GOOD.

231
00:14:12,385 --> 00:14:16,186
AGENT BAXTER WAS ARRESTED
IN COLLEGE-- POSSESSION
OF HEROIN, INTENT TO SELL.

232
00:14:16,255 --> 00:14:19,691
WELL, I GUESS WE'D BETTER
JUST DROP THE CASE RIGHT NOW.

233
00:14:19,759 --> 00:14:22,560
CASE? YOU SOUND LIKE THE FEDS.
YOU GOT YOUR 48 HOURS.

234
00:14:22,629 --> 00:14:24,695
<i> THEN YOU'RE</i>
<i> BACK IN SEATTLE.</i>

235
00:14:28,301 --> 00:14:30,734
MAY I HAVE THIS?
YOU'VE GOT IT ALL ON FILE.

236
00:14:30,804 --> 00:14:33,137
WE DON'T NEED
THIS STUFF ABOUT TODD
FLOATIN' AROUND.

237
00:14:33,206 --> 00:14:35,206
COME ON IN.

238
00:14:40,680 --> 00:14:42,780
<i> THE SHREDDERS IN SEATTLE</i>
<i> ARE SMALLER.</i>

239
00:14:42,849 --> 00:14:44,782
SECRETS IN D.C.
ARE BIGGER.

240
00:14:44,851 --> 00:14:48,286
<i>YOU SHOULD SEE THE SIZE</i>
<i>OF THE JANITOR'S CART THEY HAUL</i>
<i>THIS STUFF AWAY IN EVERY FRIDAY.</i>

241
00:14:48,354 --> 00:14:51,155
- DID TALBOT PUT HIS PERSONALITY
THROUGH THAT THING?
- [ Chuckling ]

242
00:14:51,224 --> 00:14:53,290
<i> HAVE A SEAT.</i>

243
00:14:53,359 --> 00:14:55,393
LET ME TELL YOU
SOMETHIN' ABOUT TALBOT.

244
00:14:55,461 --> 00:14:59,564
<i>YOU KNOW ALL THAT CRAP ABOUT</i>
<i>BOY SCOUTS WHO RUN ALONGSIDE</i>
<i>THE PRESIDENT'S LIMO?</i>

245
00:14:59,633 --> 00:15:03,267
HE DOESN'T JUST BUY IT.
HE LIVED IT FOR 25 YEARS.

246
00:15:03,336 --> 00:15:05,135
TODD BAXTER WOULD HAVE TOO.

247
00:15:06,805 --> 00:15:09,340
TELL ME SOMETHING.

248
00:15:09,409 --> 00:15:12,843
IF THEY WERE SUCH GOOD FRIENDS,
WHY DID SHE WALK OUT
OF THAT HOTEL ROOM?

249
00:15:14,414 --> 00:15:17,814
I DON'T KNOW.
HE HAD AN ADDICTION.

250
00:15:17,883 --> 00:15:19,751
SOMETIMES WALKING'S
THE ONLY OPTION.

251
00:15:47,847 --> 00:15:50,949
[ Screaming ]

252
00:15:52,486 --> 00:15:54,986
<i> EMILY!</i>

253
00:16:02,429 --> 00:16:06,164
[ Yelling, Groaning ]

254
00:16:08,201 --> 00:16:10,835
DAMN!
[ Groans ]

255
00:16:10,903 --> 00:16:12,903
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?
YEAH.

256
00:16:21,147 --> 00:16:25,082
THEY SAID MUGGINGS WERE UP,
BUT I HAD NO IDEA.

257
00:16:25,151 --> 00:16:27,084
THANKS.

258
00:16:27,153 --> 00:16:29,654
I'M GLAD
YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.
THANK YOU.

259
00:16:33,627 --> 00:16:37,261
THAT WASN'T A MUGGING.
I THINK YOU KNOW THAT.

260
00:16:38,498 --> 00:16:41,432
WHY DID YOU LEAVE TODD
AT THE HOTEL THAT NIGHT?

261
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:45,403
WHAT DO YOU WANT FROM ME?
HE WAS MY FRIEND. IT'S NOT
MY FAULT HE COULDN'T SEE THAT.

262
00:16:45,472 --> 00:16:49,674
HE WAS MURDERED,
AND SOMEONE IS TRYING TO DESTROY
WHAT'S LEFT OF HIS NAME.

263
00:16:49,743 --> 00:16:52,243
<i>I DON'T THINK YOU WANT THAT.</i>

264
00:16:52,312 --> 00:16:54,212
WHY ARE YOU LYING?

265
00:17:00,319 --> 00:17:02,119
[ Sighs ]

266
00:17:07,293 --> 00:17:09,961
<i> I CAME TO THIS TOWN</i>
<i> TO MAKE A DIFFERENCE.</i>

267
00:17:10,029 --> 00:17:11,929
YOU SOUND LIKE TODD.

268
00:17:14,534 --> 00:17:18,936
- YOU KNEW HIM?
- HE SAVED MY LIFE ONCE.

269
00:17:24,177 --> 00:17:26,644
[ Sobs ]
GOD, I MISS HIM.

270
00:17:26,713 --> 00:17:29,347
THEN HELP ME.

271
00:17:29,416 --> 00:17:31,916
HELP ME
PROTECT HIS MEMORY.

272
00:17:34,854 --> 00:17:37,955
<i> [ Sighs ]</i>

273
00:17:40,960 --> 00:17:43,895
TODD SAID HE WAS MEETING
SOMEONE AT THE HOTEL,

274
00:17:43,963 --> 00:17:47,898
BUT HE STILL HAD TIME
TO HELP ME WITH A PROBLEM
I HAD AT WORK.

275
00:17:47,967 --> 00:17:50,068
THAT WAS TODD.

276
00:17:50,137 --> 00:17:52,937
WE HAD DINNER AND I LEFT.

277
00:17:53,005 --> 00:17:56,174
I HADN'T HEARD FROM HIM
IN A WEEK, AND THEN...

278
00:17:56,243 --> 00:17:58,175
I SEE THE NEWS.

279
00:17:58,244 --> 00:18:00,745
WHEN THEY FOUND HIS BODY.

280
00:18:02,916 --> 00:18:06,451
I GET THIS PHONE CALL.
THE MAN ON THE OTHER END
KNOWS WHERE I LIVE.

281
00:18:06,519 --> 00:18:08,953
HE KNOWS WHERE I WALK MY DOG,
EVERYTHING.

282
00:18:09,022 --> 00:18:11,689
HE ASKED YOU TO LIE.
HE HAD THE LIE WORKED OUT.

283
00:18:11,758 --> 00:18:13,691
IT WAS SCARY.

284
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:16,527
<i>I HAD TO SAY THAT</i>
<i>IT WAS SEX AND HEROIN.</i>

285
00:18:16,596 --> 00:18:19,530
TODD AND I WERE BEST FRIENDS.
JUST FRIENDS.

286
00:18:19,599 --> 00:18:23,167
WE WERE NEVER TOGETHER
IN HIS ROOM THAT NIGHT,
AND HE NEVER DID DRUGS.

287
00:18:23,236 --> 00:18:26,036
THEY SAID HE WAS ARRESTED
FOR POSSESSION IN COLLEGE.

288
00:18:26,105 --> 00:18:28,539
A TOTAL LIE.

289
00:18:28,608 --> 00:18:31,609
THE MAN ON THE PHONE
THREATENED TO END MY CAREER.
I DIDN'T CARE.

290
00:18:31,678 --> 00:18:34,679
TODD WAS MY FRIEND.
I TOLD HIM I WAS GONNA
CALL THE PAPERS.

291
00:18:35,982 --> 00:18:38,316
AND THEN HE TOLD ME
TO CHECK MY MAILBOX.

292
00:18:47,360 --> 00:18:49,994
<i>THAT'S MY FATHER.</i>

293
00:18:54,835 --> 00:18:58,837
THEY MADE ME CHOOSE
BETWEEN TODD'S MEMORY
AND MY FATHER'S LIFE.

294
00:19:00,874 --> 00:19:02,740
I--
[ Exhales ]

295
00:19:02,809 --> 00:19:05,209
YOU DID THE RIGHT THING.

296
00:19:05,278 --> 00:19:08,313
YOU DID
THE RIGHT THING.

297
00:19:17,056 --> 00:19:19,923
DID TODD TELL YOU
WHO HE WAS MEETING
THAT NIGHT?

298
00:19:19,992 --> 00:19:21,759
NO. UH--

299
00:19:21,827 --> 00:19:26,530
<i>[ Emily ]</i>
<i>ALL HE SAID WAS, "I'M GONNA</i>
<i>BE IN THE PAPER SOON."</i>

300
00:19:26,599 --> 00:19:28,699
<i>AND THEN HE TAPPED</i>
<i>HIS BRIEFCASE.</i>

301
00:19:30,770 --> 00:19:33,871
LIKE THERE WAS
SOMETHING IMPORTANT IN IT.

302
00:19:36,910 --> 00:19:39,844
I WANT YOU TO
STAY AT MY PLACE.

303
00:19:39,913 --> 00:19:41,912
YOU'LL BE SAFE THERE.

304
00:19:43,616 --> 00:19:46,550
THERE'S NO SAFE PLACE
FROM THE MONSTERS.

305
00:19:46,620 --> 00:19:49,353
<i> TODD SAID D.C. WAS LIKE</i>
<i> A BIG MASQUERADE BALL,</i>

306
00:19:49,422 --> 00:19:51,622
ONLY THE PEOPLE IN DISGUISE
WERE MONSTERS.

307
00:19:51,691 --> 00:19:54,692
<i> IF YOU WANT TO MAKE</i>
<i> A DIFFERENCE, YOU GOTTA</i>
<i> PULL OFF A FEW MASKS.</i>

308
00:19:54,760 --> 00:19:56,961
THAT'S WHY HE'S DEAD, JAROD.

309
00:19:58,031 --> 00:19:59,530
<i>[ Angelo ]</i>
<i>NO HOPE.</i>

310
00:20:00,800 --> 00:20:02,800
NO HOPE.

311
00:20:06,372 --> 00:20:09,307
WHAT IS "HOPE,"
ANGELO?

312
00:20:09,375 --> 00:20:11,976
SYDNEY LOST HOPE.

313
00:20:12,045 --> 00:20:14,045
SYDNEY LOST HOPE.

314
00:20:14,114 --> 00:20:17,815
- WHAT DOES IT HAVE TO DO
WITH THAT WATCH?
- CENTRE TAKES HOPE.

315
00:20:20,420 --> 00:20:22,553
WHAT DID THEY TAKE,
ANGELO?

316
00:20:28,528 --> 00:20:31,762
CHECK SYD'S FILE.
IT'S A LONG SHOT, BUT SEE IF
THERE'S SOMETHING ABOUT "HOPE."

317
00:20:31,831 --> 00:20:33,731
OKAY.

318
00:20:35,001 --> 00:20:37,602
MR. PARKER TAKES HOPE
FROM SYDNEY.

319
00:20:37,670 --> 00:20:40,838
WHAT DOES MY FATHER
HAVE TO DO WITH THIS?

320
00:20:45,445 --> 00:20:48,446
<i>[ Tires Screeching ]</i>

321
00:20:55,988 --> 00:20:58,088
[ Sobbing ]

322
00:20:58,158 --> 00:21:02,359
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>

323
00:21:08,634 --> 00:21:14,004
HEY, HOW ABOUT
I COOK YOU LUNCH?

324
00:21:14,073 --> 00:21:16,274
NO, THANKS. I'LL PASS.

325
00:21:16,343 --> 00:21:19,042
YOU HAVE YOUR VEGETABLE,
YOUR CHICKEN NOODLE,
YOUR SHRIMP GUMBO.

326
00:21:19,111 --> 00:21:21,145
SHRIMP ALMOST TASTES REAL.

327
00:21:21,213 --> 00:21:22,846
MMM.
TEMPTING, BUT NO.

328
00:21:24,350 --> 00:21:26,150
THIS BETTER BE GOOD.

329
00:21:26,219 --> 00:21:28,886
<i>TODD BAXTER TELLS HIS FRIEND,</i>
<i>EMILY SADLER,</i>

330
00:21:28,955 --> 00:21:31,021
THAT HIS NAME IS ABOUT TO BE
PUT INTO THE PAPER,

331
00:21:31,090 --> 00:21:33,291
THAT HE HAS SOMETHING
IMPORTANT IN HIS BRIEFCASE.

332
00:21:33,360 --> 00:21:36,628
<i>THREE DAYS LATER, BILL RADCLIFF,</i>
<i>REPORTER, COVERS SECRET SERVICE</i>
<i>FOR THE</i> WASHINGTON JOURNAL--

333
00:21:36,696 --> 00:21:38,362
DIES IN A CAR ACCIDENT.

334
00:21:38,431 --> 00:21:40,864
<i>AN ACCIDENT</i>
<i>WITH ONE INCONGRUOUS DETAIL.</i>

335
00:21:40,933 --> 00:21:44,702
LIGATURE MARKS,
LIKE THOSE FOUND ON TODD BAXTER.

336
00:21:44,771 --> 00:21:49,307
<i>I BELIEVE BAXTER WAS GOING</i>
<i>TO MEET THIS REPORTER TO EXPOSE</i>
<i>SOMETHING THAT HE DISCOVERED.</i>

337
00:21:49,375 --> 00:21:51,308
AND THAT "SOMETHING"
WAS IN HIS BRIEFCASE.

338
00:21:51,377 --> 00:21:53,444
ALL WE FOUND
WAS OFFICE PAPERWORK.

339
00:21:53,512 --> 00:21:55,580
WHAT MAKES YOU SO DAMN SURE?

340
00:21:55,648 --> 00:21:58,549
LET'S JUST SAY THAT
I'VE GOTTEN INTO THE MIND
OF THE KILLER.

341
00:21:58,618 --> 00:22:00,318
YOU'VE WHAT?

342
00:22:02,722 --> 00:22:06,591
THINK ABOUT IT.
THE KILLER WANTS TO COVER UP
WHAT TODD HAS DISCOVERED.

343
00:22:06,659 --> 00:22:09,660
<i> THAT'S WHY HE HAD TO</i>
<i> KILL THE REPORTER TOO.</i>

344
00:22:15,168 --> 00:22:17,101
I DON'T THINK SO.

345
00:22:17,170 --> 00:22:21,439
<i>THE KILLER'S INTO THE ACT--</i>
<i>THE POWER HE EXHIBITS</i>
<i>OVER THE HELPLESS VICTIM.</i>

346
00:22:21,507 --> 00:22:24,575
THERE'S A PURITY
IN THAT VIOLENCE.
IT SATISFIES HIM.

347
00:22:24,644 --> 00:22:27,345
I MEAN, IF THERE IS
A COVER-UP, SOMEONE ELSE
IS CALLING THE SHOTS.

348
00:22:27,414 --> 00:22:29,380
- SOMEONE ELSE?
- YES.

349
00:22:29,448 --> 00:22:32,049
- AND THIS THEORY
IS BASED UPON WHAT?
-<i> HOLD ON A SECOND. HOLD ON.</i>

350
00:22:32,118 --> 00:22:34,385
THERE ARE
TWO SUSPECTS?

351
00:22:34,454 --> 00:22:37,421
YOU TWO MIGHT WANT
TO GET ON THE SAME PAGE.
YOU'RE RUNNING OUT OF TIME.

352
00:22:38,924 --> 00:22:40,557
<i> HOLDER,</i>
<i> COME INTO MY OFFICE.</i>

353
00:22:40,626 --> 00:22:43,260
YOU AND I,
WE HAVE TO TALK.

354
00:22:43,329 --> 00:22:45,930
TALBOT COULD SHUT US DOWN.
NOT ME.

355
00:22:45,998 --> 00:22:49,634
HE COULD SEAL THE EVIDENCE.
IT WOULD TAKE MONTHS TO REOPEN
THE CASE, EVEN FOR THE F.B.I.

356
00:22:49,703 --> 00:22:52,469
YOU AND ME,
WE HAVE TO WORK TOGETHER.
YES, BUT NOT BLINDLY.

357
00:22:52,538 --> 00:22:56,307
- BUT YOU CAN MAKE THESE LEAPS
OF LOGIC? HOW DOES THAT WORK?
- IT'S COMPLICATED.

358
00:22:56,375 --> 00:22:58,976
WELL, THAT ISN'T GOOD ENOUGH.
THERE'S EVIDENCE OF A COVER-UP.

359
00:22:59,045 --> 00:23:01,112
- NOT BY THIS KILLER.
- THEN BY WHO?

360
00:23:01,181 --> 00:23:03,747
<i> TODD BAXTER</i>
<i> WAS AT THAT HOTEL ROOM</i>
<i> TO MEET THE REPORTER...</i>

361
00:23:03,816 --> 00:23:05,549
SO HE COULD
EXPOSE THE KILLER.

362
00:23:05,618 --> 00:23:09,220
- HAS IT EVER OCCURRED TO YOU
THAT MAYBE HE NEEDS TO KILL?
- "NEEDS TO KILL." NO.

363
00:23:09,289 --> 00:23:11,555
MAYBE YOU OUGHT
TO GET INTO HIS MIND AGAIN.
HOW DOES THAT WORK?

364
00:23:11,624 --> 00:23:14,192
IT'S COMPLICATED.

365
00:23:15,361 --> 00:23:17,362
[ Exhales ]

366
00:23:21,067 --> 00:23:24,301
YOU KNOW, JAROD, I THINK THAT
UNDER DIFFERENT CIRCUMSTANCES
YOU AND I--

367
00:23:24,370 --> 00:23:26,003
<i> YES?</i>

368
00:23:27,206 --> 00:23:29,473
STILL WOULDN'T HAVE
GOTTEN ALONG.

369
00:23:30,576 --> 00:23:32,577
IS THAT SO?

370
00:23:32,645 --> 00:23:36,279
WELL, FOR STARTERS,
YOU DRINK PROCESSED POWDER
AND HOT WATER.

371
00:23:36,348 --> 00:23:41,184
YOU NEVER KNOW HOW TASTY
SOMETHING'S GOING TO BE
UNLESS YOU TRY IT FOR YOURSELF.

372
00:23:41,253 --> 00:23:44,187
WELL, IF WE EVER MAKE IT
OUT OF HERE, I'M GONNA SHOW YOU
WHAT REAL FOOD IS LIKE.

373
00:23:44,256 --> 00:23:46,991
- I MAKE
AN AMAZING BOUILLABAISSE.
- REALLY?

374
00:23:47,059 --> 00:23:49,293
MM-HMM.

375
00:23:49,362 --> 00:23:52,296
- CAN YOU DRINK IT OUT OF A MUG?
- YOU CAN DRINK IT
OUT OF WHATEVER YOU LIKE.

376
00:23:57,771 --> 00:23:59,771
[ Chuckles ]

377
00:24:08,047 --> 00:24:10,748
YOU'RE LOOKIN'
FOR YOUR FAMILY?

378
00:24:10,817 --> 00:24:14,418
YES. THEY'RE OUT HERE
SOMEWHERE.

379
00:24:15,922 --> 00:24:18,856
I LOST MY DAD
WHEN I WAS 10.

380
00:24:18,924 --> 00:24:21,959
IT'S A TOUGH AGE
TO BECOME MAN OF THE HOUSE.

381
00:24:22,027 --> 00:24:25,396
YOU GREW UP FAST.
VERY.

382
00:24:25,465 --> 00:24:30,067
BUT IT TAUGHT ME RESPONSIBILITY,
TO ALWAYS DO THE RIGHT THING.

383
00:24:30,135 --> 00:24:32,269
<i> AND MAKE SURE</i>
<i> OTHERS DO TOO.</i>

384
00:24:33,272 --> 00:24:35,840
[ Chuckles ]

385
00:24:36,843 --> 00:24:40,043
<i>[ Todd ]</i>
<i>MAKE SURE OTHERS DO TOO.</i>

386
00:24:40,112 --> 00:24:42,546
<i>[ Emily ] ALL HE SAID WAS,</i>
<i>"I'M GONNA BE</i>
<i> IN THE PAPER SOON."</i>

387
00:24:42,615 --> 00:24:44,548
<i>AND THEN</i>
<i>HE TAPPED HIS BRIEFCASE.</i>

388
00:24:44,617 --> 00:24:47,317
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>LIKE THERE WAS SOMETHING</i>
<i>IMPORTANT IN IT.</i>

389
00:24:52,258 --> 00:24:54,191
DOESN'T MAKE ANY SENSE.

390
00:24:54,260 --> 00:24:58,562
<i> YOU KNOW, THE THING</i>
<i> I CAN'T UNDERSTAND</i>
<i> ABOUT THESE PAPERS, JAROD?</i>

391
00:24:58,631 --> 00:25:01,866
WHY KILL TODD OVER THESE?
THEY'RE ALL RANDOM,
NOT CONNECTED.

392
00:25:01,934 --> 00:25:05,569
NOT EVEN BY A SPECIFIC CASE.
IT'S LIKE SOMEBODY
JUST GRABBED THEM.

393
00:25:05,638 --> 00:25:08,572
TO REPLACE THE ONES
THAT WERE ORIGINALLY
IN HIS BRIEFCASE.

394
00:25:08,641 --> 00:25:13,343
IF SOMEBODY DID SWITCH 'EM,
THEN TODD DEFINITELY
HAD THE GOODS ON HIM.

395
00:25:13,412 --> 00:25:15,412
THE QUESTION IS, WHO.

396
00:25:16,849 --> 00:25:19,116
HANG IN THERE, MAN.
WE'LL GET HIM.

397
00:25:20,153 --> 00:25:22,153
<i> [ Phone Rings ]</i>

398
00:25:24,456 --> 00:25:26,456
AGENT WILKES.
IT'S MALONE.

399
00:25:26,525 --> 00:25:29,259
LISTEN, I WENT OVER
THOSE PAPERS YOU SENT
FROM BAXTER'S BRIEFCASE.

400
00:25:29,328 --> 00:25:31,262
NOTHING.

401
00:25:31,331 --> 00:25:33,630
HOWEVER,
I FOUND SOMETHING INTERESTING.
WHAT?

402
00:25:33,699 --> 00:25:35,966
THAT HEROIN CHARGE
AGAINST BAXTER
FROM HIS COLLEGE DAYS?

403
00:25:36,035 --> 00:25:37,735
IT'S A FAKE.
YEAH.

404
00:25:37,804 --> 00:25:40,437
THE CAMPUS COP
WHO ARRESTED BAXTER
DOESN'T EXIST.

405
00:25:40,506 --> 00:25:43,941
-<i> SOMEONE'S TRYING</i>
<i>  TO SMEAR HIS PAST.</i>
- I'LL HAVE TO CALL YOU BACK.

406
00:25:44,010 --> 00:25:46,377
[ Dial Tone ]

407
00:25:46,445 --> 00:25:48,412
LET'S TAKE A WALK.

408
00:25:49,615 --> 00:25:51,949
<i> LET ME SHARE SOMETHING</i>
<i> WITH YOU, AGENT.</i>

409
00:25:52,018 --> 00:25:55,252
I'M UNDER REVIEW,
AND I'M NOT INCLINED TO
BELIEVE IN A CONSPIRACY,

410
00:25:55,321 --> 00:25:57,354
BUT I KNOW WHAT CITY
I'M IN.

411
00:25:57,423 --> 00:25:59,991
IF THIS BAXTER THING
KEEPS GOIN' SOUTH,

412
00:26:00,059 --> 00:26:03,227
WE'RE GONNA
RUFFLE SOME FEATHERS,
AND WE'RE GONNA GET CLIPPED.

413
00:26:03,296 --> 00:26:06,297
WHAT ABOUT TODD BAXTER?
WHOSE FEATHERS DID HE RUFFLE?

414
00:26:06,365 --> 00:26:07,965
<i>WHAT DO YOU MEAN?</i>

415
00:26:08,034 --> 00:26:10,935
THERE WAS SOMETHING
IN HIS BRIEFCASE THAT
SOMEONE DIDN'T WANT EXPOSED.

416
00:26:11,004 --> 00:26:14,938
HE ALSO HAD HEROIN, BARBITURATES
AND SOME FUZZY HANDCUFFS.

417
00:26:15,007 --> 00:26:16,940
<i>THE KID WAS MESSED UP,</i>
<i>JAROD.</i>

418
00:26:17,010 --> 00:26:19,576
<i> I HIRED BAXTER.</i>
<i> YOU THINK I WANT</i>
<i> TO BELIEVE THIS?</i>

419
00:26:19,645 --> 00:26:23,847
HE WAS CONVICTED OF POSSESSION
IN COLLEGE. WE SHOULD TRACK DOWN
THE ARRESTING OFFICER.

420
00:26:23,916 --> 00:26:25,816
HE ALREADY DID.

421
00:26:29,922 --> 00:26:32,122
YOU TALKED TO THE OFFICER
THAT ARRESTED HIM?

422
00:26:32,191 --> 00:26:36,860
YES. I WOULD HAVE RATHER NOT.
TRUST ME.

423
00:26:39,465 --> 00:26:42,466
JERRY'S SEEN THE TRUTH
ON THIS THING
FROM THE BEGINNING.

424
00:26:44,404 --> 00:26:46,803
AND I'M BEGINNING
TO SEE IT MYSELF.

425
00:26:51,844 --> 00:26:53,944
<i>[ Emily ]</i>
<i>LINDEN SWITCHED THE FILES?</i>

426
00:26:54,013 --> 00:26:56,013
NICE THEORY.

427
00:26:56,081 --> 00:27:00,317
BUT YOU GOT NO PROOF UNLESS YOU
FIND THE ORIGINALS, AND THEY'RE
PROBABLY LONG SHREDDED BY NOW.

428
00:27:00,386 --> 00:27:04,688
WELL, THEN IT'S TIME TO
GO DIGGING THROUGH SOME TRASH.

429
00:28:24,102 --> 00:28:26,036
[ Glass Shattering ]

430
00:28:26,105 --> 00:28:29,273
- TYPICAL SHRINK.
JUST FLAT NUTS.
- LIES!

431
00:28:29,342 --> 00:28:31,274
IT WAS IN
A CENTRE EVIDENCE BAG.

432
00:28:31,343 --> 00:28:34,044
- WHO DID THE WATCH BELONG TO?
- I DON'T WANT TO RELIVE THAT.

433
00:28:34,113 --> 00:28:36,313
RELIVE WHAT?

434
00:28:38,284 --> 00:28:40,283
WE HELPED HIM.
IT WAS AWFUL.

435
00:28:40,352 --> 00:28:45,155
THEN GET IT OUT IN THE OPEN.
IT'S A BRAND-NEW DAY
AT THE CENTRE. REMEMBER?

436
00:28:45,224 --> 00:28:49,660
ALL RIGHT. YEARS AGO,
SYDNEY KILLED A WOMAN.

437
00:28:59,838 --> 00:29:03,140
<i>[ Malone ] AGENT WILKES.</i>
<i>JUST THE MAN</i>
<i>I'VE BEEN LOOKING FOR.</i>

438
00:29:05,644 --> 00:29:07,911
WHAT?

439
00:29:07,980 --> 00:29:11,015
NICE WORKING WITH YOU AGAIN.

440
00:29:11,083 --> 00:29:14,918
A YEAR AGO, YOU WORKED WITH US
ON A KIDNAPPING IN ATLANTA.
YOU USED A DIFFERENT NAME.

441
00:29:16,355 --> 00:29:18,355
WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?

442
00:29:31,204 --> 00:29:33,471
WHO ARE YOU WORKING
UNDERCOVER FOR?

443
00:29:34,640 --> 00:29:36,907
CONGRESS.

444
00:29:36,976 --> 00:29:39,209
I WORK FOR
AN OVERSIGHT COMMITTEE...

445
00:29:39,278 --> 00:29:41,411
THAT KEEPS TABS ON LOCAL
AND FEDERAL LAW ENFORCEMENT.

446
00:29:41,480 --> 00:29:45,282
THAT EXPLAINS
YOUR BADGE IN ATLANTA.
WHAT BROUGHT YOU TO THE SERVICE?

447
00:29:45,351 --> 00:29:48,485
THE COMMITTEE SMELLED A RAT
IN THE BAXTER CASE.

448
00:29:48,554 --> 00:29:50,554
THEY SENT ME DOWN.

449
00:29:51,991 --> 00:29:53,924
STILL DOESN'T ANSWER
ALL MY QUESTIONS.

450
00:29:53,993 --> 00:29:55,926
I'LL ANSWER ANY QUESTION
YOU WANT.

451
00:29:55,995 --> 00:30:00,530
BUT RIGHT NOW,
I FOUND TODD BAXTER'S KILLER,
AND I NEED YOUR HELP TO GET HIM.

452
00:30:04,369 --> 00:30:06,803
SYD KILLED A WOMAN?

453
00:30:06,872 --> 00:30:10,806
IN A CAR ACCIDENT.
IT HAPPENED DURING THE EARLY
STAGES OF THE JAROD PROJECT.

454
00:30:10,875 --> 00:30:13,443
<i> SYD HIRED A COLLEGE INTERN</i>
<i> FROM FRANCE, A YOUNG GIRL.</i>

455
00:30:13,512 --> 00:30:15,378
<i>[ Broots Exhales ]</i>
<i>SHE WAS PRETTY.</i>

456
00:30:15,446 --> 00:30:17,780
<i> APPARENTLY,</i>
<i> THEY WERE HAVING AN AFFAIR.</i>

457
00:30:17,850 --> 00:30:21,784
THEY'D GONE TO DINNER AND WERE
DRIVING BACK WHEN SYDNEY LOST
CONTROL AND BROADSIDED A TREE.

458
00:30:21,854 --> 00:30:23,786
SHE DIED TWO HOURS LATER
IN THE HOSPITAL.

459
00:30:23,855 --> 00:30:26,289
- HER NAME WAS HOPE?
- CLAUDIA.

460
00:30:26,358 --> 00:30:28,558
WHEN ANGELO SAID SYDNEY
LOST HOPE, HE MEANT IT.

461
00:30:28,627 --> 00:30:31,327
NOW, THESE ARE
THE CENTRE RECORDS
OF THE ACCIDENT.

462
00:30:31,396 --> 00:30:33,129
<i> I'M HOPING THAT'LL</i>
<i> HELP US FIND SYD.</i>

463
00:30:33,198 --> 00:30:36,599
<i>PROVENCE RESTAURANT.</i>
<i>THIS MUST BE WHERE</i>
<i>THEY DINED BEFORE--</i>

464
00:30:36,668 --> 00:30:38,735
WORTH A TRY.
YEAH.

465
00:30:40,138 --> 00:30:42,071
DID YOU GLUE THIS
TOGETHER?
YEAH.

466
00:30:42,140 --> 00:30:45,741
IT'S ALL 6,422 STRIPS.

467
00:30:45,811 --> 00:30:48,978
AFTER THAT, I GOT BORED.
MMM. YEAH, WELL,
BAXTER CERTAINLY WASN'T.

468
00:30:49,047 --> 00:30:52,782
<i> BETWEEN THESE ARTICLES AND</i>
<i> THOSE CONFIDENTIAL MEMOS</i>
<i> YOU PIECED TOGETHER,</i>

469
00:30:52,851 --> 00:30:58,755
BAXTER CONNECTED LINDEN TO
NUMEROUS ILLEGAL OPERATIONS
AND OTHER SO-CALLED SUICIDES.

470
00:30:58,823 --> 00:31:01,758
TODD WAS DEFINITELY
TRYING TO MAKE A DIFFERENCE.

471
00:31:01,826 --> 00:31:06,029
- HOW ABOUT THOSE APPLES?
-<i> THEM</i> APPLES.

472
00:31:06,098 --> 00:31:08,465
- HMM?
- IT'S "HOW ABOUT THEM APPLES?"

473
00:31:08,533 --> 00:31:11,935
OH. I KNEW IT WAS
SOMETHING ABOUT APPLES.

474
00:31:13,571 --> 00:31:16,206
<i> BAILEY TOLD ME</i>
<i> WHO YOU WORKED FOR.</i>

475
00:31:16,274 --> 00:31:19,542
THEY THE ONES WHO
SHOWED YOU HOW TO GET INTO
A KILLER'S MIND?

476
00:31:19,611 --> 00:31:22,945
NO. THAT WAS
MORE HOME SCHOOLING.

477
00:31:24,082 --> 00:31:26,349
THAT'S SOME HOME.

478
00:31:26,418 --> 00:31:29,151
YOU DON'T WANT TO KNOW.

479
00:31:29,221 --> 00:31:32,088
WELL,
I DECIDED NOT TO WAIT.

480
00:31:32,156 --> 00:31:34,090
TRY THIS.

481
00:31:34,158 --> 00:31:36,158
IS THIS
YOUR BOUILLABAISSE?
MM-HMM.

482
00:31:37,395 --> 00:31:39,395
MMM.

483
00:31:39,464 --> 00:31:41,397
MMM!

484
00:31:41,467 --> 00:31:44,233
HOW DO YOU HAVE TIME TO
TRACK A KILLER AND MAKE
SOMETHING THIS DELICIOUS?

485
00:31:44,302 --> 00:31:49,238
WELL,
WE ALL HAVE OUR SECRETS.
DON'T WE, JAROD?

486
00:32:11,129 --> 00:32:14,697
IT ONLY HELPS
UNTIL THE NEXT MORNING.

487
00:32:14,766 --> 00:32:17,600
AND, UH,
I'LL BE BACK THEN.

488
00:32:17,668 --> 00:32:19,602
WE KNOW ABOUT
THE ACCIDENT, SYD.

489
00:32:19,671 --> 00:32:22,872
<i>LOOK, I'M HERE WITH</i>
<i>SOME OF MY FAVORITE GHOSTS.</i>

490
00:32:22,941 --> 00:32:25,876
<i> CAN'T YOU SEE?</i>
<i> SO LEAVE ME ALONE.</i>

491
00:32:25,944 --> 00:32:29,712
YOU WOULDN'T
LET US OFF THAT EASY,
SO FORGET IT, SYDNEY.

492
00:32:29,781 --> 00:32:33,883
IT WASN'T YOUR FAULT.
YOU HAVE TO LET CLAUDIA GO.

493
00:32:33,951 --> 00:32:36,252
I CAN'T.
WE'RE CELEBRATING.

494
00:32:36,321 --> 00:32:38,588
WHY?

495
00:32:38,657 --> 00:32:41,157
BECAUSE.

496
00:32:41,225 --> 00:32:43,559
BECAUSE THEY USED HER
AGAINST ME.

497
00:32:43,628 --> 00:32:46,562
SYD,
THE CENTRE HELPED YOU.

498
00:32:46,631 --> 00:32:49,032
THE CENTRE SURE HELPED.

499
00:32:49,101 --> 00:32:52,569
<i> THEY WERE THERE</i>
<i> RIGHT AFTER THE ACCIDENT.</i>

500
00:32:52,637 --> 00:32:55,505
<i> CENTRE SWEEPERS YELLING,</i>

501
00:32:55,573 --> 00:32:59,442
"OH, WE'LL GIVE CLAUDIA
THE BEST CARE."

502
00:32:59,511 --> 00:33:01,378
<i>AND THEN...</i>

503
00:33:01,446 --> 00:33:04,113
TWO HOURS LATER...

504
00:33:04,182 --> 00:33:06,182
I GOT THE NEWS.

505
00:33:10,322 --> 00:33:13,256
I GAVE HER THIS WATCH
FOR HER BIRTHDAY.

506
00:33:13,325 --> 00:33:15,325
IT WOULD HAVE BEEN
YESTERDAY.

507
00:33:16,995 --> 00:33:19,729
HOW DID ANGELO KNOW
ABOUT--

508
00:33:19,798 --> 00:33:23,266
[ Chuckles ]
ANGELO.

509
00:33:23,334 --> 00:33:27,270
HOW DOES ANGELO
KNOW ABOUT ANYTHING?

510
00:33:27,339 --> 00:33:31,341
HE KNEW THAT YOU NEED TO
DEAL WITH THIS PAIN, SYD,

511
00:33:31,410 --> 00:33:33,343
THAT YOU WERE
IN LOVE WITH HER.

512
00:33:33,412 --> 00:33:35,345
<i> THAT WASN'T ANGELO.</i>

513
00:33:35,413 --> 00:33:39,015
- THEY TOLD YOU THAT.
- THAT'S WHAT MY FATHER SAID.
THAT'S WHAT THE FILE SAID.

514
00:33:39,083 --> 00:33:42,285
CENTRE LIES!
CAREFUL, SYDNEY.

515
00:33:42,354 --> 00:33:47,123
<i>OH, NO, MUCH LATER,</i>
<i>WHEN I FOUND OUT WHAT THE CENTRE</i>
<i>WAS DOING WITH JAROD'S WORK,</i>

516
00:33:47,192 --> 00:33:49,125
<i> AND I ROSE UP IN PROTEST--</i>

517
00:33:49,194 --> 00:33:50,960
THEY USED THE ACCIDENT
AGAINST YOU?

518
00:33:51,029 --> 00:33:53,196
I DID LOVE HER.

519
00:33:53,265 --> 00:33:56,599
<i> LIKE MY DAUGHTER.</i>
<i> SHE WAS MY STUDENT.</i>

520
00:33:56,668 --> 00:34:02,271
<i> BUT THE CENTRE</i>
<i> FABRICATED SOME STORY</i>
<i> OF AN AFFAIR BETWEEN US.</i>

521
00:34:02,340 --> 00:34:04,641
THEY THREATENED ME
WITH JAIL.

522
00:34:04,709 --> 00:34:07,510
<i> THEY THREATENED--</i>
TO SEPARATE YOU
FROM JAROD.

523
00:34:07,579 --> 00:34:11,681
<i> YES.</i>
<i> THEY USED IT TO FORCE ME</i>
<i> TO DO THEIR BIDDING.</i>

524
00:34:11,750 --> 00:34:16,886
<i> NOT ONLY WAS CLAUDIA DEAD,</i>
<i> BUT THEY TRIED TO DESTROY</i>
<i> THE VERY MEMORY OF HER.</i>

525
00:34:18,022 --> 00:34:20,022
MY FATHER
DID THIS TO YOU?

526
00:34:20,091 --> 00:34:23,293
NOT DIRECTLY, OF COURSE.

527
00:34:23,361 --> 00:34:27,830
BUT, YES, MR. PARKER
WAS RUNNING THE CENTRE.

528
00:34:27,899 --> 00:34:30,800
<i> NOW HAVE A SHOT.</i>

529
00:34:48,719 --> 00:34:51,221
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>TODD BAXTER KNEW TOO MUCH.</i>

530
00:34:51,289 --> 00:34:55,124
HE CONNECTED LINDEN
TO SEVERAL MAJOR
ILLEGAL OPERATIONS--

531
00:34:55,193 --> 00:34:57,693
CHARACTER ASSASSINATIONS,
EXTORTION,

532
00:34:57,762 --> 00:35:00,096
<i>AMONG OTHER</i>
<i>CLANDESTINE THINGS.</i>

533
00:35:00,164 --> 00:35:03,833
<i>YOUR DIRECTOR OF COMMUNICATIONS</i>
<i>HAS HAD SIX WASHINGTON JOBS</i>
<i>IN THE LAST SEVEN YEARS.</i>

534
00:35:03,901 --> 00:35:07,670
YEAH. TRAVEL OFFICE,
D.O.J. COVER-UP, FRAMED
A D.O.E. WHISTLE BLOWER.

535
00:35:07,739 --> 00:35:10,240
WATERGATE PLUMBERS
GOT NOTHIN' ON THIS GUY.

536
00:35:10,308 --> 00:35:13,309
<i>HASN'T PAID THIS WELL SINCE</i>
<i>G. GORDON LIDDY. HIS OFFSHORE</i>
<i>ACCOUNTS ARE PACKED.</i>

537
00:35:13,378 --> 00:35:16,646
AGENT BAXTER FOUND OUT,
AND THAT CRAFTY
SON OF A BITCH KILLED HIM.

538
00:35:16,715 --> 00:35:19,448
<i>MADE IT LOOK LIKE</i>
<i>A DRUG OVERDOSE</i>
<i>SO I'D SHUT DOWN THE CASE.</i>

539
00:35:19,517 --> 00:35:23,352
HE PLAYED ME.
EXCEPT LINDEN ISN'T
THE KILLER, IS HE, RACHEL?

540
00:35:23,421 --> 00:35:26,222
ARE YOU TWO READING
EACH OTHER'S MINDS NOW?

541
00:35:26,290 --> 00:35:28,290
MURDER IS NOT
IN LINDEN'S PROFILE.

542
00:35:28,359 --> 00:35:31,728
<i>HE LIKES TO CONTROL THE TRUTH,</i>
<i>BUT ONLY FROM THE BACKGROUND.</i>
<i>HE WAS NEVER IN THAT HOTEL.</i>

543
00:35:31,797 --> 00:35:35,765
THINK HE HAD SOMEONE
DO HIS DIRTY WORK FOR HIM?
MM-HMM.

544
00:35:35,834 --> 00:35:39,702
ALL RIGHT.
WHEN DO WE MOVE?
[ Both ] WE DON'T.

545
00:35:39,771 --> 00:35:45,008
THERE'S A KILLER OUT THERE,
AND LINDEN IS GOING TO
LEAD US RIGHT TO HIM.

546
00:35:50,448 --> 00:35:53,549
DADDY, THE CENTRE DID THIS.
YOU DID THIS.

547
00:35:53,618 --> 00:35:56,585
YOU FORGOT.
THE TRIUMVIRATE GAVE THE ORDERS.
I CARRIED THEM OUT.

548
00:35:56,654 --> 00:36:00,190
- I KNEW YOU WOULD SAY THAT.
- I DON'T LIKE YOUR ATTITUDE.

549
00:36:00,258 --> 00:36:05,095
DADDY, PLEASE.
I JUST WANT SYDNEY
TO HAVE SOME CLOSURE.

550
00:36:05,163 --> 00:36:07,363
[ Sighs ]
IT CAN BE ARRANGED.

551
00:36:09,267 --> 00:36:12,601
-<i> [ Intercom Beeps ]</i>
- MR. MORGENSTERN.

552
00:36:22,547 --> 00:36:24,547
[ Gasps ]

553
00:36:25,917 --> 00:36:30,753
CLAUDIA.
[ Speaking French ]

554
00:36:32,023 --> 00:36:35,724
[ French ]
OH, SYDNEY.

555
00:36:35,793 --> 00:36:37,961
<i> [ French Continues ]</i>

556
00:36:38,029 --> 00:36:41,431
WHEN YOU TOLD ME WHAT
SYDNEY WAS GOING THROUGH,
I HAD HER FLOWN IN.

557
00:36:41,499 --> 00:36:45,667
<i>SHE'S A GROUNDBREAKING</i>
<i>PSYCHIATRIST AT A TEACHING</i>
<i>HOSPITAL OUTSIDE OF PARIS.</i>

558
00:36:47,305 --> 00:36:49,572
A HOSPITAL FUNDED
BY THE CENTRE.

559
00:36:49,641 --> 00:36:53,843
AFTER THE ACCIDENT,
SHE HEALED UP QUICKLY.
WE GAVE HER A FUTURE, A CAREER.

560
00:36:53,912 --> 00:36:56,612
AND TOLD HER THAT
SYDNEY WAS DEAD.

561
00:36:56,681 --> 00:37:00,850
WELL, THAT'S ONE ORDER
I WISH I'D NEVER TAKEN.

562
00:37:00,918 --> 00:37:03,886
ANGEL, A NEW LIFE
CHANGES EVERYTHING.
I TOLD YOU.

563
00:37:03,955 --> 00:37:05,988
IT'S A BRAND-NEW DAY.

564
00:37:21,673 --> 00:37:24,507
<i> [ Rings ]</i>
COMMUNICATIONS.
LINDEN.

565
00:37:24,576 --> 00:37:27,710
[ Jarod ]
I'M WATCHING YOU.

566
00:37:27,779 --> 00:37:29,712
WHO THE HELL IS THIS?

567
00:37:29,780 --> 00:37:33,783
I'M THE MAN YOU HIRED
TO THROW TODD BAXTER
OUT THE WINDOW.

568
00:37:37,322 --> 00:37:39,689
BAXTER COMMITTED SUICIDE.
NO.

569
00:37:39,757 --> 00:37:41,724
YOU HIRED ME TO KILL HIM,
DIDN'T YOU?

570
00:37:43,561 --> 00:37:45,728
I'LL TAKE THAT
AS A "NO COMMENT."

571
00:37:45,797 --> 00:37:49,965
IF YOU CARE
TO EXPLAIN YOURSELF,
OFF THE RECORD,

572
00:37:50,034 --> 00:37:52,801
MEET ME AT
THE RIVER GLEN HOTEL,

573
00:37:52,870 --> 00:37:55,371
ROOM 814.

574
00:38:04,082 --> 00:38:06,015
HELLO?

575
00:38:09,720 --> 00:38:12,554
HELLO?
ANYONE HERE?

576
00:38:16,994 --> 00:38:20,696
YOU DON'T THINK
I'D BE FOOLISH ENOUGH
TO BE ARMED, DO YOU?

577
00:38:20,765 --> 00:38:24,099
I'M ABOUT TO FIND OUT
HOW BIG A FOOL YOU ARE.

578
00:38:24,168 --> 00:38:26,835
AGENT WILKES.

579
00:38:26,904 --> 00:38:30,573
SO WHAT IS THIS?
IT'S THE RIVER GLEN HOTEL.

580
00:38:30,642 --> 00:38:35,244
NOT EXACTLY THE WATERGATE,
BUT SCANDALS CAN BE
MADE HERE AS WELL.

581
00:38:37,949 --> 00:38:41,751
WELL, I SURE HOPE YOU BROUGHT
YOUR WALLET SO YOU CAN BUY
YOUR FREEDOM.

582
00:38:41,819 --> 00:38:43,653
INNOCENT MEN
DON'T NEED TO.

583
00:38:43,721 --> 00:38:46,688
[ Jarod ]
THESE DOCUMENTS THAT
I STOLE FROM YOUR OFFICE--

584
00:38:46,757 --> 00:38:48,791
THEY SEEM
TO SAY OTHERWISE.

585
00:38:56,634 --> 00:38:58,634
WELL, AREN'T YOU
INDUSTRIOUS.

586
00:39:01,506 --> 00:39:04,173
FABRICATIONS DESIGNED
TO DESTROY AN HONEST MAN.

587
00:39:04,242 --> 00:39:06,342
LIKE THE ONES
YOU CREATE?

588
00:39:06,410 --> 00:39:09,012
LIKE THE ONES
THAT TODD BAXTER
DISCOVERED?

589
00:39:09,080 --> 00:39:12,481
YOU MAKE A FORTUNE
CREATING SCANDALS
THAT RUIN PEOPLE'S LIVES,

590
00:39:12,550 --> 00:39:14,650
EVEN END THEM.

591
00:39:14,719 --> 00:39:18,621
JAROD, IF YOU'RE TRYING
TO GET ME TO MAKE
A VERBAL ADMISSION...

592
00:39:18,690 --> 00:39:21,123
FOR SOMETHING
I KNOW NOTHING ABOUT,

593
00:39:21,192 --> 00:39:23,525
FOR YOU OR...

594
00:39:23,594 --> 00:39:25,995
WHOEVER ELSE IS WATCHING--

595
00:39:26,064 --> 00:39:27,963
DAMN IT.

596
00:39:31,236 --> 00:39:33,302
I'M AFRAID YOU GOT
THE WRONG FOOL.

597
00:39:33,371 --> 00:39:36,305
[ Sighs ]
YOU'RE RIGHT.

598
00:39:38,209 --> 00:39:41,877
I AM A FOOL FOR EVER
BELIEVING YOU COULD POSSIBLY
JUST TELL THE TRUTH.

599
00:39:41,946 --> 00:39:45,348
- WE'RE DONE HERE.
- OH, WE ARE JUST...

600
00:39:46,450 --> 00:39:48,217
GETTING STARTED.

601
00:39:50,388 --> 00:39:53,389
WE'D BETTER
GET IN THERE.
NO, JUST GIVE HIM A MINUTE.

602
00:39:55,259 --> 00:39:58,661
- I WOULDN'T WANT YOU
TO MISS IT.
- MISS WHAT?

603
00:40:00,231 --> 00:40:02,432
YOUR SUICIDE.

604
00:40:05,936 --> 00:40:07,870
[ Gasps ]

605
00:40:08,939 --> 00:40:11,273
[ Grunts ]

606
00:40:11,342 --> 00:40:13,876
[ Sighs ]

607
00:40:13,945 --> 00:40:17,313
♪♪ [ Whistling ]

608
00:40:21,619 --> 00:40:24,220
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

609
00:40:24,289 --> 00:40:26,955
I'M SETTING THE SCENE,

610
00:40:27,024 --> 00:40:29,558
JUST LIKE THE MAN YOU HIRED
TO KILL TODD BAXTER DID.

611
00:40:29,627 --> 00:40:32,128
[ Groans ]

612
00:40:32,196 --> 00:40:34,997
I'M GONNA MAKE IT SEEM
LIKE YOU HAD AN EVENING
OF... DRUGS.

613
00:40:35,066 --> 00:40:38,467
<i>THEN YOU TOOK A SWAN DIVE</i>
<i>OUT THE WINDOW.</i>

614
00:40:38,535 --> 00:40:41,637
HOPE THEY FIND
YOUR BODY SOONER.

615
00:40:41,706 --> 00:40:45,374
NO, WAIT. WAIT! NO!
MMM. NO WAITING.

616
00:40:49,414 --> 00:40:52,214
NO! NO!
[ Grunts ]

617
00:40:52,283 --> 00:40:54,950
WHO DID IT? YOU TELL ME
WHO KILLED TODD BAXTER,

618
00:40:55,019 --> 00:40:58,321
OR THEY'LL BE FISHING YOUR BODY
OUT OF THE POTOMAC--
WHAT'S LEFT OF IT.

619
00:40:58,389 --> 00:41:01,857
I CAN PAY YOU.
JUST FORGET ABOUT BAXTER.
MONEY?

620
00:41:01,926 --> 00:41:03,993
<i> YEAH.</i>
TODD BAXTER
SAVED MY LIFE!

621
00:41:04,062 --> 00:41:07,896
YOU KILLED HIM.
I'M GONNA EVEN THE SCORE!
NO! YOU'RE CRAZY.

622
00:41:07,965 --> 00:41:11,500
PLAN "B." PLAN "B."
GO TO PLAN "B"!

623
00:41:11,568 --> 00:41:14,870
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
YOU WARNING YOUR ACCOMPLICE?

624
00:41:14,939 --> 00:41:18,874
YOU TELL ME WHO KILLED HIM,
OR I WILL DROP YOU
OUT OF THIS WINDOW!

625
00:41:18,943 --> 00:41:22,277
HOLDER. AGENT HOLDER.

626
00:41:22,346 --> 00:41:25,748
WHERE IS HE?
HE'S IN THE SERVICE ELEVATOR
AT THE END OF THE HALL.

627
00:41:25,817 --> 00:41:28,350
GET UP!
NO! NO! NO!

628
00:42:01,285 --> 00:42:03,686
GOOD LUCK.
YEAH, YOU TOO.

629
00:42:13,798 --> 00:42:15,798
IS THIS
MORE BOUILLABAISSE?

630
00:42:15,866 --> 00:42:19,067
NO, I ONLY HAD 30 SECONDS.
IT'S CHICKEN NOODLE.

631
00:42:19,136 --> 00:42:21,403
[ Laughs ]
THE CHICKEN
ALMOST TASTES REAL.

632
00:42:22,974 --> 00:42:24,974
MMM.

633
00:42:32,383 --> 00:42:34,649
THAT'S WHY
YOU'RE UNDERCOVER.

634
00:42:34,718 --> 00:42:37,520
<i> YOU'RE ALONE</i>
<i> IN THIS WORLD.</i>

635
00:42:37,589 --> 00:42:39,521
WE ALL HAVE SECRETS.

636
00:42:41,358 --> 00:42:44,526
NO FAMILY?
NO ONE TO GET CLOSE TO?

637
00:42:46,698 --> 00:42:50,533
NOT YET.
I SHOULD GET BACK
TO THE OFFICE.

638
00:42:50,601 --> 00:42:54,637
JAROD. THIS-- THIS WAS MORE
THAN JUST A CASE FOR YOU.

639
00:42:54,705 --> 00:42:56,505
WHY?

640
00:42:57,808 --> 00:43:01,944
LET'S JUST SAY
I WAS HELPING OUT...
AN OLD FRIEND.

641
00:43:05,049 --> 00:43:08,283
WELL, IF YOU EVER
NEED A NEW FRIEND,
YOU CAN CALL ME.

